comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: I was in Coffs Harbour yesterday (19/10/10), and had lunch (6" Subway) in this park to check it out. Nothing dramatic to report - the trees have grown, the bridges rebuilt, and the tide was low, unlike the high tide here. Google Maps Satellite - maps.google.com.au/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&...

comment.author: 53306716@N06
comment._content: The (now old) bridge piers and how they impact on the flow of water into the creek has been the source of much talk in Coffs.  An 2009 article from the local paper (http://www.coffscoastadvocate.com.au/story/2009/12/15/pier-pressure-put-on-council/) describes the situation.
